Not all heroes wear capes!
Happy Mother's Day to the most loving, patient, and kind mother I know, @little.hummingbirds 

Besides being an amazing mother, she is an amazing human.

Where we live in Kelowna, there is a guy we all know as "Jeff The Baloon Guy". He's alone, in a wheelchair, but he's always at the farmers market making balloons for kids bringing smiles to their faces. In fact, we even hired him for our daughter's birthday.

A couple of weeks ago, Fehren found out he was homeless. Some issues left him sleeping in his car with only a few items to call his own.

As soon as Fehren found out, she not only opened up our guest suite for him and bought a wheelchair ramp that he could use to go in and out of the door but also called around to find some more permanent housing for him.

We're happy to report that he is in that housing and doing well.

She would never tell you this story as she doesn't like being in the limelight, but today I thought the world should know what an amazing woman she is.

To all the amazing mothers out there, you need more than one day to be recognized for all you do, but today we are reminded of the superhero you really are.

Don't compete in saturated industries. Create your own.

It's hard to stand out in a saturated industry. 

There are already a lot of established businesses, and it can be difficult to get noticed.

Instead, try to create your own category. This means finding a niche that hasn't been filled yet and becoming the go-to expert in that area.

Uber is a great example of this. 

They were the first company to create a ride-sharing service, and they quickly became the leader in the industry.

If you can create your own category, you'll have a much better chance of success. 

You'll be the first one to market, and you'll be able to set the rules.

Creating your own category is not easy, but it's worth it in the long run. 

It's one of the best ways to achieve success in business.

#createayourowncategory #nichemarketing #expertpositioning #success

Want to stand out from your competition?

Offer a money-back guarantee!

This is a great way to mitigate the risk for potential customers and show them that you're confident in your product or service.

Of course, you don't want to make your guarantee too easy to qualify for. You want to make sure that customers are putting in the effort to use your product or service before they ask for a refund.

But if you're confident in what you're offering, a money-back guarantee is a great way to show potential customers that you're serious about helping them.

Offering a money-back guarantee is a great way to build trust with potential customers and show them that you're committed to their satisfaction.

#moneybackguarantee #customersatisfaction #trustbuilding #standoutfromyourcompetition

Want to land high-paying clients?

Here are 5 things you need to do:

1. Target your marketing. Who is your ideal client? What are their pain points and desires? Tailor your marketing messages accordingly.

2. Create a valuable offer. What problem can you solve for your clients? What transformation can you help them achieve? Make sure your offer is worth the investment.

3. Differentiate yourself from your competitors. What makes you unique and better than the competition? Highlight your unique selling proposition in your marketing and sales materials.

4. Build trust and credibility. Show potential clients that you're the expert and that you can deliver on your promises. Share case studies, testimonials, and other social proof.

Believe in your offer. If you don't believe in what you're selling, it will be difficult to convince others to do so. 

Be passionate about your work and believe in the value you can provide to your clients.

If you're struggling to land high-paying clients, DM me and I'll see how I can help.

#highpayingclients #salestips #marketingtips #businesstips

Social proof is better than good copy. Collect testimonials and endorsements from past clients to show potential clients that you can help them.

Getting clients is great, but keeping them is even better.

And the best way to keep clients is to provide them with so much value that they can't imagine going anywhere else.

So focus on the quality of your delivery. Make sure that you're giving your clients everything they need to succeed.

When you focus on providing value, your clients will be more likely to stay with you for the long term. And that's the key to building a successful business.

#valueadd #customerretention #clientretention #businesssuccess

Marketing is not about convincing people to do something they don't want to do.

It's about finding people who already want what you have to offer.

That means understanding your target audience and their needs. It means creating content and messaging that resonates with them. And it means making it easy for them to say yes.

#marketingtips #targetaudience #contentmarketing #socialmediamarketing

Save time and scale your business with one-to-many sales calls.

Instead of spending hours on one-to-one sales calls, host group sales calls where you can sell to multiple people at once. This will free up your time so you can focus on other aspects of your business.

To get started, simply:

Schedule a group sales call using a platform like Zoom or Google Meet.

Create a presentation that introduces your product or service and explains its benefits.

Be prepared to answer any questions that the group may have.

Offer a call to action, such as a free trial or a discount.

One-to-many sales calls are a great way to scale your business and reach more potential customers.

#salestips #scalingsmallbusiness #onlinesales #socialmediamarketing

Don't sell your offer. Sell the solution to your prospect's problem.

Your prospect doesn't care about how great your offer is. They only care about how it can help them solve their problem or achieve their goal.

When you're selling, focus on the benefits of your offer and how it will make your prospect's life better. Don't just list features and specs. Tell your prospect a story about how your offer can help them achieve their desired outcome.

1. Don't need a funnel. Focus on solution seekers and offer them a simple solution.

3. Be different, not better. Create a category where you're the only player and you won't need to compare prices or features.

Are you over complicating the sales process?

Don't sell yourself short!

If you're always trying to convince prospects how you're different or better than your competitors, it means your offer isn't unique enough.

Instead, focus on creating an offer that is so unique and different that it's a no-brainer for prospects to sign up with you.

Once you have a unique offer, you won't have to convince prospects. They'll be eager to do business with you because you're the only one who can offer them what they need. 🏆

#UniqueOffer #nobrainer🚫🧠

The more steps you add to your sales process, the more you repel premium clients.

Premium clients are willing to pay a premium for your services because they want fast solutions. 

They don't want to waste their time jumping through hoops.

If you want to attract premium clients, keep your sales process simple and straightforward. 

Offer a clear solution to their problem and make it easy for them to buy from you.

#PremiumClients #SimpleSalesProcess #CustomerService

Create the following 3 types of content to get the best bang for your buck:

1. Videos that answer the most FAQs in your space.

2. Videos that answer questions your prospect SHOULD be asking (but don't know to ask).

3. A ""Founder's"" video, a testimonial mashup video, and a ""Buy My Stuff"" or ""Book A Call"" video.

By creating this type of content, you can build trust, authority, and relationships with your audience, which will lead to more sales and conversions.

#ContentMarketing #7x7x3Formula #VideoContent

Struggling to attract your ideal client?

Ask yourself these two questions:

Does my marketing speak directly to my target audience on a consistent basis?

Does my marketing portray me as an authority figure in my niche?

If you can answer yes to both of these questions, then you're on the right track.

By following these tips, you can attract your ideal clients and grow your business.

#MarketingTips #AttractIdealClients #GrowYourBusiness

Positioning is how you show your prospects why your product or service is uniquely valuable and worth investing in. It's not just about what you do, but why it matters.

Poor positioning can cost you thousands of dollars in lost revenue. When you're not clear about what makes you different and special, prospects are more likely to see you as a commodity and choose the cheapest option.

By following these tips, you can position yourself as the go-to choice for your target market and command premium prices.

Which of these tips helped you the most?

Don't focus on yourself - Focus on your prospect.

If you're attached to the outcome of a sale, it's easy to lose sight of the big picture. The more you focus on yourself and your commission, the less likely you are to close the deal.

Instead, focus on your prospect's needs and how you can help them. What are their pain points? What are their goals? Once you understand their perspective, you can tailor your pitch to their specific needs.

Here's a simple tip: Ask more questions than you give answers. The more you learn about your prospect, the better equipped you'll be to help them.

Remember, sales is about helping people, not selling them things. When you focus on your prospect's needs, the sale will naturally follow.

#salestraining #salestips #salesmotivation

“Never play somebody else's game"When you play somebody else's game, you're conceding the upper hand. You're agreeing to their rules, their terms, and their goals. And if you're not careful, you'll find yourself playing to their strengths and not your own.That's why, if you want to win the game in business, you need to create your own game. You need to set your own rules, your own terms, and your own goals. And you need to play to your own strengths.Follow for more.

Identifying a problem you can easily solve in the market and presenting the true value to your ideal prospects is essential to getting them to show up on your sales calls.

You need to understand your target audience and their needs. 

What are their pain points? 

What challenges do they face? 

Once you know what problems they have, you can start to think about how your product or service can solve them.

Once you have a good understanding of the problem you're solving, you need to communicate the value of your solution to your prospects in a clear and concise way. 

What benefits will they get from using your product or service? 

How will it make their lives easier or better?

This is how you make them show up.

Follow for more.

Amazon's Holiday Dash book is a great example of this. It's a book for kids that showcases all the toys that Amazon is selling this holiday season. The kids see the book, they want the toys, and the parents end up buying them.

This same principle can be applied to premium services. For example, if you run a Mastermind company, you could send customized invitation letters to your prospects' spouses and families. This shows that you're thinking of the whole person and their needs, and it makes it more likely that they'll be supportive of their spouse's decision to join your Mastermind.

Here's another example: let's say you sell a software service to businesses. Instead of just selling to the CEO, you could also sell to the CFO, the COO, and other key stakeholders. This way, everyone is on the same page and there's more buy-in for your product or service.

By selling to the influencer, you can make the sales process easier and increase your chances of closing deals.

When selling a high-ticket product or service to premium prospects, it's important to remember that it's never about the cost. It's always about the value.

What kind of value are you offering your prospects? Will your product or service help them achieve their goals? Save them time or money? Make their lives easier?

If you can clearly articulate the value of your product or service, price becomes less of a factor.

Selling high-ticket items to premium prospects can be challenging, but it's definitely possible. By focusing on the value, being confident, and providing excellent customer service, you can increase your chances of success.

#highticketsales #premiumpspects #value #confidence #customerservice

Pixel brokering: a secret weapon for reaching more customers

Have you ever heard of pixel brokering? 

It's a way to reach a targeted audience that's already interested in what you have to offer, by partnering with complementary businesses or industry influencers and sharing your custom audiences with each other.

It's a great way to increase your reach and get more leads and sales, and it's something that I require of all my clients.

Partner with complementary businesses. 

Partner with industry influencers.

Pay niche bloggers or content creators to put your pixel on their website. 

Pixel brokering is a great way to boost your marketing results without having to spend a lot of money on advertising. So, if you're not already using it, I highly recommend checking it out.

#pixelbrokering #marketingtips #reachmorecustomers

Here's to a new perspective, folks! Considering Return on Effort (RoE) alongside Return on Investment (ROI).💡

Wondering where to put your energy? Paid ads vs. organic growth? The answer, in short, it depends!

If time is on your side, grow organically. 🌱

But if you can spare some coins, paid ads could bring swift returns. It's all about balance. 

What matters is knowing which metric is of utmost value to you. ⚖️💵 

#MarketingMinds #RoEvRoI #TimeIsMoney

Premium prospects don't care about extra bells and whistles. 🔔

They want something simple, high-quality, and that will solve their specific problem. 🎯

So, instead of adding more to your offer, focus on making what you already have even more valuable. 

How can you make your offer more exclusive?
